  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a very high heat</p><p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>beef strips</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>cornflour</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min without stirring to get colour on one side of the beef</p><p>After 1-2 min, turn the beef and cook for 1-2 min further or until browned all over</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1624269236895-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1624269236895-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1624269236895-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1624269236895-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1624269236895-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>browned beef</strong> to a plate and set aside</p><p>Tip: Don't worry if it's not fully cooked yet, it'll go back in the sauce later!</p><p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat and once hot, add the<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped pepper & onion</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1624269240864-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1624269240864-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1624269240864-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1624269240864-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1624269240864-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the veg is softening, combine the<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ketchup</strong> and <strong>rice vinegar</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>sticky chilli sauce</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>edamame & jasmine rice </strong>to a large, heatproof bowl and put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 2-3 min or until piping hot</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1624269245918-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1624269245918-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1624269245918-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1624269245918-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1624269245918-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has started to soften, return the <strong>browned beef </strong>to the pan and pour in the <strong>sticky sauce</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min further until the sauce has thickened slightly and has coated everything nicely – this is your <strong>sticky chilli beef</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624269250651-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624269250651-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624269250651-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624269250651-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624269250651-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sticky chilli beef</strong> over the <strong>edamame & jasmine rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 5,
